Sentencas: Dense BaCe0.8Sm0.2O2.90 (BCSO) thin films were successfully fabricated on porous NiO-BCSO substrates by dry pressing process.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on proton conducting Sm-doped BaCeO3 electrolyte thin film

Sentencas: As characterized by scanning electron microscope, the BCSO films were about 50 gm.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on proton conducting Sm-doped BaCeO3 electrolyte thin film

Sentencas: With Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCF) as cathodes, single cells were tested at 600 and 700 degrees C with humidified (3% HB2O) hydrogen as fuel and oxygen as oxidant.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on proton conducting Sm-doped BaCeO3 electrolyte thin film

Sentencas: The open circuit voltage of 1.049 V at 600 degrees C and 1.032 V at 700 degrees C were achieved, indicating negligible gas permeation through the BCSO thin films.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on proton conducting Sm-doped BaCeO3 electrolyte thin film

Sentencas: Maximum power densities of 132 and 340 mW/cm(2) were obtained at 600 and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on proton conducting Sm-doped BaCeO3 electrolyte thin film

Sentencas: The impedance measurements at open circuit conditions showed that there were two rate-limiting processes for the electrode reactions and that the cell performances were essentially determined by the electrode polarization resistances at temperature below 650 degrees C, which implied that it was essential to reduce the electrode polarization by developing novel electrode materials to improve the performance of ITSOFC based on BCSO electrolyte.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on proton conducting Sm-doped BaCeO3 electrolyte thin film

Sentencas: Conductivities of BCSO under the cell operating circumstances were obtained as 0.00416, 0.00662 and 0.00938 Scm(-1) at 500, 600 and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on proton conducting Sm-doped BaCeO3 electrolyte thin film

Sentencas: The activation energy of BCSO conductivity was calculated as 29.5 and 43.8 kJ/mol for the temperature range of 550-700 degrees C and of 400-550 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on proton conducting Sm-doped BaCeO3 electrolyte thin film

Sentencas: Endurance test was firstly carried out with 75 mu m BCSO electrolyte at 650 degrees C at the operating voltage of 0.7 V and current density about 0.12 A/cm(2).
Titulo: Electrochemical properties of intermediate-temperature SOFCs based on proton conducting Sm-doped BaCeO3 electrolyte thin film
